<paragraph blockId="45.[264,1323,284,1906]" box="[312,1187,1562,1588]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Etymology. Hausa language 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[648,747,1562,1587]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sadaukii">
<emphasis box="[648,747,1562,1587]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">sadaukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, noun in apposition, for bold warrior.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[264,1323,284,1906]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Distribution (
<tableCitation box="[470,571,1602,1628]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="9.[264,343,851,872]" captionText="TABLE 1. Distribution of Afroestricus species by country." pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Tables 1</tableCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[588,605,1602,1628]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="10.[264,343,563,584]" captionText="TABLE 2. Phenology of Afroestricus species. Abbreviations refer to the months of the year." pageId="45" pageNumber="46">2</tableCitation>
; 
<figureCitation box="[620,724,1602,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 194" captionStartId="70.[264,357,1870,1891]" captionTargetBox="[459,1150,1206,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-93@70.[411,1177,1171,1869]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 194. Distribution of six species of Afroestricus in Africa and Madagascar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050679/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Fig. 194</figureCitation>
). Found in a few localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1084,1160,1602,1628]" name="Ghana" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Ghana</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry box="[264,355,1642,1668]" name="Nigeria" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
; collected in July­August and November
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[264,1323,284,1906]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
Remarks. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[430,677,1681,1706]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sadaukii">
<emphasis box="[430,677,1681,1706]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Afroestricus sadaukii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from congeners by the characters in the key and the combined characters of the terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[762,931,1721,1747]" captionStart="FIGURES 111–120" captionStartId="44.[264,370,1821,1842]" captionTargetBox="[290,1282,599,1796]" captionTargetId="figure-134@44.[281,1305,592,1813]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 111–120. Afroestricus sadaukii, sp. n. Male terminalia: 111–113. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views. 114. Gonostylus. 115–116. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral views. Female terminalia: 117–118. Dorsal and ventral views. 119. Spermatheca. 120. Genital fork." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5050651" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5050651/files/figure.png" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Figs. 111–120</figureCitation>
). It is further distinguished by the stout anterior acrostichal setae which are about as long as the pedicel and scape combined; four to five long, wide spaced, dorsocentral bristles, the first being well anterior to the transverse suture, and the presence of mostly or entirely yellow bristles below the middle and hind femora.
</paragraph>
